Police were searching Wednesday for the driver who struck a pedestrian on Gulf-to-Bay Boulevard and kept driving. The crash happened about 9:17 p.m. Tuesday in the eastbound lanes of Gulf-to-Bay Boulevard just east of Belcher Road, according to the Clearwater Police Department. A 50-year-old man was found lying in the road with severe injuries and later died at Mease Countryside Hospital, police said. Police have not released the manâ€™s name. Detectives as of Wednesday did not have any information about the driver and the vehicle involved in the crash. Police asked anyone with information on the case to call 727-562-4242.